-- Maruti Suzuki Production Constraints Leave Sales Shortfall, Mint Reports
-- B y   U n n i   K r i s h n a n
-- 2010-10-01T02:14:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/maruti-suzuki-production-constraints-leave-sales-shortfall-mint-reports.html
India’s largest car maker Maruti
Suzuki India Ltd. isn’t able to meet demand for its vehicles
because of production constraints, the Mint reported, quoting
Managing Executive Officer Mayank Pareek.  The company isn’t able to produce as much as 25 percent of
units sold each month, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Unni Krishnan in New Delhi at 
